**Arduino Code for Rover (Obstacle Avoidance + Basic RL Simulation****)**

// Arduino Rover Code - Smart Mars Rover AI

#include <NewPing.h>

#define TRIGGER_PIN 9

#define ECHO_PIN 10

#define MAX_DISTANCE 200

#define ENA 5

#define ENB 6

#define IN1 7

#define IN2 8

#define IN3 11

#define IN4 12

NewPing sonar(TRIGGER_PIN, ECHO_PIN, MAX_DISTANCE);

void setup() {

  pinMode(ENA, OUTPUT);

  pinMode(ENB, OUTPUT);

  pinMode(IN1, OUTPUT);

  pinMode(IN2, OUTPUT);

  pinMode(IN3, OUTPUT);

  pinMode(IN4, OUTPUT);

  Serial.begin(9600);

}

void loop() {

  delay(50);

  int distance = sonar.ping_cm();

  

  if (distance > 0 && distance < 20) {

    stop();

    delay(300);

    turnRight();

    delay(500);

  } else {

    moveForward();

  }

}

void moveForward() {

  digitalWrite(IN1, HIGH);

  digitalWrite(IN2, LOW);

  digitalWrite(IN3, HIGH);

  digitalWrite(IN4, LOW);

  analogWrite(ENA, 150);

  analogWrite(ENB, 150);

}

void stop() {

  digitalWrite(IN1, LOW);

  digitalWrite(IN2, LOW);

  digitalWrite(IN3, LOW);

  digitalWrite(IN4, LOW);

}

void turnRight() {

  digitalWrite(IN1, LOW);

  digitalWrite(IN2, HIGH);

  digitalWrite(IN3, HIGH);

  digitalWrite(IN4, LOW);

}

Wiring Diagram (Simple Description)

| **Component** | **Connection** |
| --- | --- |
| Ultrasonic Sensor Trigger | Arduino Pin 9 |
| Ultrasonic Sensor Echo | Arduino Pin 10 |
| Motor Driver ENA | Arduino Pin 5 |
| Motor Driver IN1 | Arduino Pin 7 |
| Motor Driver IN2 | Arduino Pin 8 |
| Motor Driver ENB | Arduino Pin 6 |
| Motor Driver IN3 | Arduino Pin 11 |
| Motor Driver IN4 | Arduino Pin 12 |
| Motor Driver + Battery + Motors | Usual power connections |

**Mini Project Report (Short Format)**

**Title:**

Smart Mars Rover AI

**Abstract:**

This project builds a miniature autonomous rover that can navigate obstacles using AI principles. By integrating Deep Q-Learning concepts with Arduino microcontrollers, we demonstrate a scalable model for future space exploration.

**Introduction:**

Space exploration requires autonomous systems capable of making decisions independently. Our Smart Mars Rover combines simple AI algorithms with basic hardware to achieve obstacle avoidance.

**Methodology:**

- Designed AI agent using Deep Q-Learning simulation in Python.

- Adapted learned logic to Arduino C++ environment.

- Implemented obstacle detection using Ultrasonic Sensors.

- Controlled movement with Motor Driver circuits.

**Results:**

- Rover successfully navigated an obstacle course.

- Learned to turn and adjust path based on surroundings.

**Future Work:**

- Expand to real-time terrain mapping.

- Add solar charging systems.

- Upgrade processor to Raspberry Pi for visual intelligence.

**Conclusion:**

This project shows how even basic AI combined with electronics can create powerful exploratory robots. Our rover acts as a stepping stone toward building smarter Mars exploration vehicles.

